# Docs planning conventions

## Domain mapping expectation

- When adding a new concept to `docs/concepts/**`, include a short mapping to:
  - a **module** from `docs/architecture/bankcore-module-catalog.md` (e.g., `Core::Posting`, `Teller`), and
  - whether it is **MVP** or **post-MVP** per `docs/concepts/01-mvp-vs-core.md`.

## ADR triggers (suggest an ADR when…)

- Posting/ledger invariants change, reversals strategy changes, or a new **money movement** pathway is introduced.
- A new **integration** pathway touches posting (ACH/wire/card/file ingestion), even if implementation is later.

## Writing style

- Prefer crisp invariants ("must never…", "always…") over long narrative.
- Include at least one **worked example** (sample event type + payload shape + resulting posting outline) when documenting operational flows.
- Use [docs/adr/0000-template.md](/docs/adr/0000-template.md) for preferred ADR format.
